    en: "Mendon administers building permits under Chapter 241 of the Town Code, which adopts the NYS Uniform Code. The Building Department is at the Mendon Town Hall, located inside the Village of Honeoye Falls. The town and the village are separate jurisdictions for code enforcement despite sharing the same building address.\n\nRoofing permit triggers. A full roof replacement, a structural repair, a change in roof type (asphalt to metal, for example), or work that changes the roof structure typically requires a permit. A minor patch or a shingle repair usually does not. The Building Department has the current line. Roof installations have to meet the state Uniform Code, which covers wind uplift, ice and water shield, underlayment, and flashing.\n\nEnvironmental Protection Overlay Districts (EPODs). Mendon designates certain areas — streams, steep slopes, wetlands, scenic roads — as EPODs with additional protections. A project inside an EPOD needs a separate EPOD permit on top of any building permit. The Building Department checks EPOD status when a permit application comes in; calling ahead to confirm EPOD status before starting a project avoids surprises.\n\nContractor insurance. A contractor working in Mendon needs current general liability insurance and workers' compensation coverage. The Building Department asks for proof at permit application. A contractor who is not insured cannot get a permit.\n\nHomeowner self-work. A homeowner performing roofing work on a single-family home they own and occupy is generally allowed under state rules. A permit and inspection still apply. Roofing work carries real fall and weather risks — a homeowner choosing self-work weighs the risks against the cost of hiring a pro. The statewide roofing-residential-ny entry covers the worker protection rules that apply to anyone doing the work.\n\nVillage of Honeoye Falls boundary. The village inside Mendon runs its own code enforcement office. Addresses inside the village go through Honeoye Falls, not Mendon. A property's mailing address (Honeoye Falls, NY 14472) does not always match the jurisdiction. The tax assessor confirms which office covers a specific address. The roofing-residential-ny-mon-honeoye-falls-village entry covers the village rules.\n\nInspection flow. A Mendon town inspector performs the inspection — the town does not use third-party agencies for roofing. Inspections may happen at tear-off (when the old material is off and the deck is visible) and at final.\n\nFailed inspection or unpermitted work. The Town Code Enforcement Officer can require corrections, tear-out, or a full redo when a roof was installed without a permit or does not meet code. Unpermitted roofing can block a future certificate of occupancy check and can create problems at resale.\n\nState-level rules. Wage theft protections (Labor Law 191 and 193), the Scaffold Law for elevated work (LL 240 and 241(6)), mechanic's liens for unpaid work (Lien Law 3 and 10), and General Business Law 349 for deceptive contractors all apply in Mendon as they do statewide. The roofing-residential-ny entry covers the statewide layers."
